About Us

Lizzie Healy is a first-year student in the Data Science and Analytics program at Georgetown University. She previously attended Haverford College where she earned a B.A. in Quantitative Economics with a minor in Applied Mathematics. Her senior thesis focused on the United States entertainment industry investigating the impact of director quality on the monetary and critical success of a film.

She is from Swarthmore, Pennslyvania where she lives with her parents, Dan and Lisa, and her two older brothers, Joe and Luke. She previously played division 3 collegiate lacrosse and now enjoys playing recreational sports including paddle, pickleball, and soccer. In addition, she is a novice biker, an avid reader, a non-stop music listener, and a self-proclaimed movie enthusiast.

Rachna Rawalpally is a first-year student in the Data Science and Analytics program at Georgetown University. She was previously working as a business systems analyst in San Francisco for a pharmaceutical company. Before that, she attended UC Riverside, where she received her B.S. in Statistics with a concentration in pure statistics.

She considers herself from South Carolina and California. She enjoys anything that has pretty scenery, like the beach, and trying new restaurants. Her biggest passion is watching movies and television. She hopes to secure a job in order to afford all the streaming services.
